    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-09-06T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-09-06T16:00:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9947a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-09-06T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 6, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>192. Please telegraph me your estimate of the bearing of the statements made in
                    the addresses at the opening of the Diet<note n="6" xml:id="d577fn6">Cf. reports
                        in <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_364">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, pp. 364</ref>–<ref
                            target="frus1931-41v01#pg_369">69</ref>.</note> upon the question of the
                    existence of a “state of war” and your estimate of the probable reaction in
                    Japan and effects upon Japan of a proclamation, if and when, by this Government
                    putting into effect the initial provision or more of the Neutrality Resolution
                    of May 1, 1937,<note n="7" xml:id="d577fn7">50 Stat. 121.</note> together with
                    any comments you may feel moved to offer on the question of the advisability of
                    such action now.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
